 Analysis of Literature 

17
00:01:04,510 --> 00:01:09,790
You don't have the copies or anything like that, right?

18
00:01:09,790 --> 00:01:14,260
Even if you did, there's nothing we can do.

19
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:17,280
It's not like we haven't been betrayed before.

20
00:01:18,820 --> 00:01:20,270
Well...

21
00:01:20,270 --> 00:01:23,000
No, it's okay. You can leave.

22
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:28,940
Shouldn't you give me a receipt for returning the textbooks?

23
00:01:28,940 --> 00:01:30,130
What?

24
00:01:30,130 --> 00:01:33,480
What if you say you didn't receive them later?

25
00:01:36,730 --> 00:01:39,430
D-Don't you trust adults?

26
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:51,990


27
00:01:59,010 --> 00:02:03,700
 Lee Si Wu returned textbooks 

28
00:02:05,570 --> 00:02:08,860
Here. Happy? Go now.

29
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:20,050
Why aren't you leaving?

30
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:22,150
Sign this, too.

31
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:36,420
 Park Gi Seong 

32
00:02:45,780 --> 00:02:47,560
Lee Si Wu,

33
00:02:51,790 --> 00:02:55,140
write that you won't release our textbooks.

34
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:58,080
 Episode 8  
 Here.

35
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,570
What's this?

36
00:02:59,570 --> 00:03:04,290
I thought you should get a new tablet.

37
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:07,050
Why would you...

38
00:03:07,850 --> 00:03:10,770
I bought one while I was getting a new phone.

39
00:03:10,770 --> 00:03:14,410
It looked pretty, and it reminded me of you.

40
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,190
Director.

41
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:20,890
Come on. Take it.

42
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:29,230
I got a job offer from another academy.

43
00:03:33,770 --> 00:03:35,280
Really?

44
00:03:36,370 --> 00:03:38,010
When?

45
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:42,170
Recently, unfortunately.

46
00:03:42,170 --> 00:03:46,310
But take this, still.

47
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:51,120
There's such a thing as a goodbye gift.

48
00:03:53,450 --> 00:03:57,150
I want something bigger when it comes to that.

49
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:02,670
- If so— 
 - I'm not leaving.

50
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,420
Really?

51
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:09,150
- Should I?
 - No, it's not that.

52
00:04:09,150 --> 00:04:12,430
Give this to Nam Jeong Mi instead.

53
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:15,530
- Ms. Nam?
 - She's working harder than anyone.

54
00:04:15,530 --> 00:04:19,850
Encourage the new teachers, too.

55
00:04:22,320 --> 00:04:25,180
I knew I was right about you.

56
00:04:26,260 --> 00:04:29,450
Team Leader Seo, you're a superior person.

57
00:04:29,450 --> 00:04:32,100
You're caring and courageous.

58
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:38,080
It's not that. I really want to grow the Huiwon High class.

59
00:04:40,460 --> 00:04:43,250
- I have a class soon.
 - Yes, you should get going.

60
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:46,410
It's your busy day. I'm sorry.

61
00:04:51,420 --> 00:04:52,980
Wait.

62
00:04:52,980 --> 00:04:55,450
By chance,

63
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:59,780
can you tell me where you got the job offer?

64
00:05:00,810 --> 00:05:02,880
What do you think?

65
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,610
- By chance-
- By chance?

66
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:08,150
Choeseon Korean?

67
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:30,830
Gray Witch, that cunning old woman.

68
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:34,890
Send an announcement to the mothers of Chanyeong High.

69
00:05:34,890 --> 00:05:38,590
There's no special lecture for the finals this time.

70
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:45,420
Can't another teacher still have a lecture instead of you?

71
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,910
Mr. Park.

72
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:52,820
are you telling me to eat the crumbs right now?

73
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:56,630
I'm sorry.

74
00:05:56,630 --> 00:06:00,760
Bring the Chanyeong High material I looked through last time.

75
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:03,340
Okay, I will.

76
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:05,920
You can leave.

77
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:09,790
Okay. Well, by the way...

78
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:14,000
Here.

79
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,310
What is it?

80
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:18,280
Have a look.

81
00:06:24,710 --> 00:06:26,920
What's this?

82
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:31,440
I got it from Lee Si Wu when he came to return the textbooks.

83
00:06:31,440 --> 00:06:33,810
I wonder if he's resentful because he's poor,

84
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:36,590
or maybe he's overcompensating for his insecurity.

85
00:06:36,590 --> 00:06:38,340
He wasn't regretting his action at all—

86
00:06:38,340 --> 00:06:41,480
Did he write this of his own volition?

87
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:45,480
No, I told him to write it.

88
00:06:58,930 --> 00:07:00,630
Get out.

89
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,150
Hey.

90
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:12,710
Honor, reputation,

91
00:07:12,710 --> 00:07:15,670
prestige, pride, or money.

92
00:07:18,030 --> 00:07:20,330
Which of those did you get out of this?

93
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:25,840
How dare you get this piece of crap in the name of Choeseon Korean?

94
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:27,820
From a kid?

95
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:29,120
I'm sorry.

96
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:31,020
Get out.

97
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:34,310
Get out of my face forever!

98
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:38,090
I-I'm sorry.

99
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,650
Teacher.

100
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:58,390
Hey, how's everything?

101
00:07:58,390 --> 00:08:01,200
Did you see the class material I sent?

102
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:07,680
Yes, it's true. Ms. Seo seemed concerned.

103
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:10,270
It's not like I'm a kid.

104
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:17,000
See you next week.

105
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:34,840
 Study hard wherever you go. 

106
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,860
 I'll always support you. 

107
00:08:36,860 --> 00:08:39,590
 Choi Hyeong Seon of Choeseon Korean. 

108
00:08:42,490 --> 00:08:45,280
Is Team Leader Seo worried about something?

109
00:08:46,130 --> 00:08:49,030
It's about a Huiwon High student who's coming from Choeseon Korean.

110
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:51,710
She saw him returning the textbooks.

111
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:58,760
I should nag a bit.

112
00:08:59,660 --> 00:09:01,220
At me, do you mean?

113
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:03,450
No, Team Leader Seo.

114
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:07,500
I know she made up her mind, but going there openly

115
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,660
would cause people to talk.

116
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,380
Why?

117
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:19,210
I thought you knew her plan.

118
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:25,300
She changed her mind.

119
00:09:28,570 --> 00:09:31,390
She told me she was going.

120
00:09:31,390 --> 00:09:34,980
You should hear directly from her. I don't want to speak for her.

121
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:39,340
Oh, okay.

122
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:45,240
Oh, thanks for the information.

123
00:09:47,090 --> 00:09:49,820
Go home, you goofballs.

124
00:09:49,820 --> 00:09:52,410
- Good luck.
 - Thanks.

125
00:09:53,370 --> 00:09:56,830
 I'll wait for you until you're done with the morning class. 

126
00:09:56,830 --> 00:09:59,220
 I hope you come. 

127
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:04,840
Did you promise a ratio adjustment or other incentives?

128
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:06,600
No.

129
00:10:11,930 --> 00:10:16,080
She apparently wants to focus on the Huiwon High class.

130
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:19,400
How could that be the reason?

131
00:10:20,530 --> 00:10:24,430
I looked through her contract one more time.

132
00:10:24,430 --> 00:10:28,770
I made it difficult for her to take the students with her,

133
00:10:28,770 --> 00:10:31,910
but maybe you should warn her—

134
00:10:31,910 --> 00:10:34,590
- Assistant Director. 
  - Yes.

135
00:10:34,590 --> 00:10:38,980
We shouldn't be berating someone who's on our side right now.

136
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:41,780
Berate?

137
00:10:41,780 --> 00:10:43,680
How could you say that?

138
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:46,500
Gosh, what a world.

139
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:48,940
The academy industry is like a jungle.

140
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,370
That's what I'm saying.

141
00:10:50,370 --> 00:10:55,100
Especially at times like this, we should provide the teachers

142
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:58,630
with unwavering trust and support. Don't you think?

143
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:24,810
We have ten minutes left. Should we look at another short text?

144
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,350
Or not?

145
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:39,890
But I highly recommend the text at the end.

146
00:11:39,890 --> 00:11:41,490
I knew it.

147
00:11:41,490 --> 00:11:45,090
You did, right? It's Erich Fromm's "The Art of Loving."

148
00:11:45,090 --> 00:11:50,340
"Love is the active concern for the life and the growth of that which we love."

149
00:11:50,340 --> 00:11:52,850
You can find that great sentence in there.

150
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:57,290
It's proof of my deep love for you, right?

151
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:46,290
Have you eaten?

152
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:49,260
I'm full without eating right now.

153
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:52,510
I brought a boxed lunch. Let's share it.

154
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:54,500
It's for two people.

155
00:12:55,420 --> 00:13:00,010
I don't think you brought the other half for me.

156
00:13:00,010 --> 00:13:02,120
You're right.

157
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:06,120
I won't return the favor for eating that, okay?

158
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:09,450
You sure are shrewd.

159
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:24,440
The house will feel so empty once Jun Ho moves out.

160
00:13:30,470 --> 00:13:34,750
There's no point in working so hard to raise a son.

161
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:42,070
 A captain named James Cook. 

162
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:47,730
Looks like he's planning to come home early before he moves out, at least.

163
00:13:47,730 --> 00:13:49,970
He must have some conscience.

164
00:13:51,950 --> 00:13:54,200
- I'm home.
 - You're home early.

165
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,160
- I'm back.
 - What's that?

166
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:57,740
I wanted to start packing.

167
00:13:57,740 --> 00:13:58,820
Already?

168
00:13:58,820 --> 00:14:02,020
I don't want to wait until the class starts and rush.

169
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:03,150
Hey, but still...

170
00:14:03,150 --> 00:14:05,360
I had dinner, Mom. I'll let you rest.

171
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:06,990
Good night.

172
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:11,090
Give me the lunch box.

173
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:13,990
What's that?

174
00:14:13,990 --> 00:14:17,640
I found a good side dish store.

175
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:21,070
Look.

176
00:14:21,070 --> 00:14:24,400
I brought this from home since it's the best drinking snack.

177
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:26,780
But I didn't know you wouldn't be drinking.

178
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:30,780
Sorry. My throat gets dry if I drink when I have a morning class.

179
00:14:30,780 --> 00:14:34,180
You're so unbelievable.

180
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:38,030
By the way, why did you want to see me on the weekend?

181
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:41,660
For some reason, I didn't want to go back to the empty house tonight.

182
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:44,040
Do you feel lonely, too?

183
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:46,740
Do you think I'm not a human?

184
00:14:46,740 --> 00:14:51,830
Should we start working on the blind date project again?

185
00:14:53,330 --> 00:14:57,880
Should I? I'll get you the ones with the best qualifications.

186
00:14:57,880 --> 00:15:00,210
I'm too old.

187
00:15:01,250 --> 00:15:04,000
I don't deserve to be in a relationship.

188
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:07,270
Hey, even people in nursing homes date,

189
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:11,340
have love interests, and love triangles. Don't you know?

190
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:16,010
Even when I go to a nursing home, I won't be a center of romance.

191
00:15:16,010 --> 00:15:18,760
I think I'll just watch others' romance.

192
00:15:20,610 --> 00:15:23,410
Why would you say something so scary?

193
00:15:23,410 --> 00:15:26,530
I don't know. I feel like that stuff has nothing to do with me.

194
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:28,130
Why?

195
00:15:29,310 --> 00:15:31,330
Why?

196
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:37,550
Why? Why? Why? Why?

197
00:15:38,490 --> 00:15:40,150
I think...

198
00:15:42,010 --> 00:15:45,290
my cogwheels are misaligned.

199
00:15:45,290 --> 00:15:47,090
What cogwheels?

200
00:15:48,190 --> 00:15:51,940
People around the same age tend to

201
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:55,410
have similar tasks they're facing, you know.

202
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:58,220
Entering college is the priority until high school.

203
00:15:58,220 --> 00:16:01,890
Studying or dating is important in college.

204
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:05,500
You worry about getting a job when you're about to graduate,

205
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:07,750
- and when that's set, you start considering marriage. 
-  Yes.

206
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:11,020
And if you get married and have a kid, you worry about the college entrance again.

207
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:15,060
That's right. But when my college classmates were studying and dating,

208
00:16:15,060 --> 00:16:20,370
I worked my butt off to make money. I hadn't even graduated when you took the bar exam.

209
00:16:21,130 --> 00:16:23,070
Seriously.

210
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:28,050
The debt collectors were after us every day, but my brother hadn't finished his studies.

211
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:31,120
When I was free from debt,

212
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:34,060
I started prioritizing my students' college entrance. So

213
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:37,720
my clock was a bit out of sync with others, right?

214
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:43,310
So, you think you'll continue to be out of sync until you go to the nursing home?

215
00:16:43,310 --> 00:16:47,310
I've been working hard

216
00:16:47,310 --> 00:16:49,900
on each task in my life,

217
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:52,970
but I never got to have a proper relationship. It's unfair.

218
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:55,800
I'm just saying it's unfair.

219
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:58,470
You sound really cowardly right now.

220
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:03,930
I passed the first round of the bar exam when I was hot and heavy with my husband.

221
00:17:03,930 --> 00:17:05,710
Don't you remember?

222
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,080
Right.

223
00:17:08,890 --> 00:17:10,800
I remember.

224
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:13,100
It was a hot summer.

225
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:17,170
Not only was there no AC but there was no soundproofing in that tiny student apartment.

226
00:17:17,170 --> 00:17:21,610
- So crazy.
 - It was so sticky and hot.

227
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:25,140
For some reason, I didn't want to wear even the thinnest clothes.

228
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:26,210
Seriously.

229
00:17:26,210 --> 00:17:28,210
- It didn't matter who initiated— 
 - Stop, stop, stop.

230
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:31,670
- I was like—
 - Stop! Why do I have to listen to this?

231
00:17:31,670 --> 00:17:33,810
Drink. Drink.

232
00:17:35,090 --> 00:17:40,680
You had to mature faster than others,

233
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:45,840
but I don't think that's why you didn't get to date.

234
00:17:47,010 --> 00:17:48,520
What is it, then?

235
00:17:49,910 --> 00:17:55,060
You're either a fool who has too many expectations for love,

236
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:59,350
or a fool who looked down on love too much.

237
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:04,820
Which one do you think I am?

238
00:18:04,820 --> 00:18:06,790
You looked down on it.

239
00:18:08,450 --> 00:18:13,510
I'm really impressed you paid off that much debt at a young age,

240
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:16,710
but you became pretty successful, too. Money, car, and home.

241
00:18:16,710 --> 00:18:18,970
Money, car, and home.

242
00:18:18,970 --> 00:18:23,060
You got everything people value, one by one.

243
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:26,080
It's easy to even fool yourself

244
00:18:26,080 --> 00:18:29,020
by saying, "I don't need love."

245
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,840
I pretended to be cool a lot.

246
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,340
Yes.

247
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:38,710
After being like that, it gets a bit embarrassing to say,

248
00:18:38,710 --> 00:18:43,070
"I want to be in love, too."

249
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:47,080
That's why you have no choice but to lie to yourself again.

250
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:50,110
But...

251
00:18:51,260 --> 00:18:54,170
what if I keep lying to myself,

252
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:59,550
but I don't buy the lie anymore?

253
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:01,750
What do I do then?

254
00:19:05,480 --> 00:19:08,050
Does this have to do

255
00:19:08,050 --> 00:19:10,980
with what you mentioned before?

256
00:19:12,400 --> 00:19:15,670
You said you can't go back to the past anymore.

257
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:20,690
Just one can would be okay, right?

258
00:19:28,910 --> 00:19:30,530
Tasty.

259
00:19:57,140 --> 00:20:01,510
It really could've been dangerous today. You know I've been acting like his mentor.

260
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:05,570
But I almost had lunch with him after I finished the class early today.

261
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:07,410
It was so hard to hold back.

262
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:10,990
So what if you have a lunch with him?

263
00:20:10,990 --> 00:20:15,140
